
137

On the road from Shaffhausen to Munich
we pass Hills of Basalt & [unclear]porphyry similar[/unclear]
to the [unclear]Lungano[/unclear] Hills so that on the NW.
S & SE side of the Alps are effects
that may with even probability be referred to
igneous than to any other cause.- Indeed it is
a probable hypothesis that the Weight of the
Alps & the appenines have prevented the fire
from bursting out except in their confines where the pressure

was least

